# Build-context excludes for `docker build -f deploy/hub/Dockerfile .` (context =
# repo root). The hubd Dockerfile does `COPY . .` in its build stage; without
# this, secrets and huge state trees would be sent to the daemon and baked into
# the intermediate build layer (the final distroless image only copies /hubd, but
# the build layer is still leakable if cached/pushed). Keep this tight.

# Secrets — MUST never enter the build context (public-repo hygiene).
.env
.env.*
**/*.local.md

# Sprawl agent state + worktrees (can be very large; may contain secrets/logs).
.sprawl/

# VCS + build artifacts.
.git/
.gitignore
sprawl
hubd

# Node / SPA build inputs (the embedded SPA seam is empty this slice).
**/node_modules/

# Editor/OS cruft.
*.swp
.DS_Store
